citeinfo.title: INFRA_ROADS

descript.abstract: This GIS layer for all roads (including tourist roads, management tracks and firebreaks) in the Kruger National Park.
descript.purpose: Roads data have been captured and processed for cartographic production and spatial analysis by scientists undertaking research in the Kruger National Park.
descript.supplinf: It is our intention to maintain roads in our database which have fallen into disuse. These are important for historical analysis as they formed boundaries to burn-blocks, ranger sections and other regional divisions.

procstep.procdesc: Source data as supplied by Surveys and Mapping were converted by GIMS from ReGIS format to ARC/INFO coverages, cleaned and built (tolerances unknown). They were also edge-matched and the national datum transformation from Cape to Hartebeesthoek94 datum was applied with an accuracy higher than that of the actual data.

Roads outside the Park were clipped out of the coverage. An old roads layer from GIS Lab was converted to Shapefile and then Coverage format. The national datum conversion was undertaken (0.5m accuracy). The new roads layer (from Surveys & Mapping via GIMS) was considered spatially accurate but incomplete; the old layer was complete with attributes but spatially inaccurate. The two layers were combined using ArcView to yield the current road layer.
